e path where: (1) early in Round 0 the players test the market with relatively safe, near-fair trades, (2) elephant quickly realizes that selling RED for GREEN is profitable and leans into that, (3) turtle becomes increasingly willing to pay for RED as the end approaches, and (4) pig behaves cooperatively, accepting clearly beneficial offers and sometimes getting crowded out when both pig and turtle want cheap RED from elephant. This yields several RED-for-GREEN trades, mostly from elephant to pig and turtle, with proposals gradually becoming more aggressive but still individually rational given their beliefs and the random-tie-breaker rule.",
