ally give away a lot of value if multiple recipients accept, while more analytically strong and search-oriented players (like monkey) are more likely to push for high-gain trades, especially dumping green for red/blue. We forecast a path where (1) gorilla tests moderate, slightly value-creating trades but is reluctant to part with red, (2) camel actively arbitrages red into blue and sometimes uses green as a bargaining chip, and (3) monkey aggressively tries to turn green into red/blue and opportunistically accepts profitable trades, with some offers declined when the proposer pushes too far beyond what others are willing to concede.",
